  "prompt": "Who were the lawyers who navigated legal issues for Lyft and/or Uber?",
  "response": "Several lawyers and law firms have been involved in navigating legal issues for Lyft and Uber over the years. Here are a few notable names:\n\n### Uber:\n1. **Tony West** - Uber's General Counsel. He previously served as Associate Attorney General of the United States.\n2. **Salle Yoo** - Former Chief Legal Officer and General Counsel at Uber.\n3. **Matt Kallman** - Former Head of Communications & Policy Legal at Uber.\n\n### Lyft:\n1. **Kristin Sverchek** - General Counsel at Lyft.\n2. **Adam Rogoff** - Former Deputy General Counsel at Lyft.\n3. **Katie Wattengold** - Former Associate General Counsel at Lyft.\n\n### Law Firms:\nBoth companies have also utilized several external law firms to handle various legal issues:\n1. **Perkins Coie LLP** - Provided legal services for both Uber and Lyft.\n2. **Cooley LLP** - Known to have represented Lyft.\n3. **Gibson, Dunn & Crutcher LLP** - Represented Uber in multiple cases.\n\nThese lawyers and firms have worked on a wide range of legal issues, including regulatory compliance, employment law, intellectual property disputes, and more.",
